Hey guys! We are now enrolling for November classes! There is still some availability in each class, though they're filling quickly. We'd love to have you with us! To register or ask any questions: Please email me at SarahDowlingCasting@gmail.com and put November Classes in the subject line! 

**

We are now registering for our November Zoom workshops and would love for you to join us! Classes are kept intentionally small to maximize the workshop time and provide feedback to each person throughout the class! We look at the back-end of casting software - what a casting director sees when you send your tapes and materials via email or through services like Actors Access, and what the client sees when your material is sent to them! We also cover Scene Study and Improv, and all things business related - auditions, materials, self-tapes etc.  

 I am a 20-year veteran casting director.  My classes are very much tailored to the students who are in them each month. We delve into commercial casting: how to figure out the storyboards and scripts you're sent to audition, how to figure out the tone they're looking for and how to make sure your tapes look like they should for submission. We also do a deep dive into film casting: how to discern the tone and pacing of the script, how to fully inhabit the character and how to make sure your tape captures all of it. 

**This is a business class (taught by a casting director with 20+ yeas experience) offering practical real-life to help actors get representation, widen their representation into other markets, and get more auditions, call backs and bookings.

Please let me know if you have any questions or would like to join us! You can email me at SarahDowlingCasting@gmail.com with any questions or to register! Let me know which day or days are best for you when you email!  Looking forward to working with you! 

Thanks so much,

Sarah

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì BOULDER, CO**
**Shoot Date:** Saturday, October 26 (6 days away)
**Project:** *Under My Eyelids* ‚Äì a heartfelt short film about an ex professional skateboarder reflecting on his memories of skateboarding after a severe TBI.

**ROLE:** Kid Cody (Boy, 9‚Äì11)
‚Äì Curious, brave, and a little shy.
‚Äì Comfortable standing or riding on a skateboard (no tricks required).
‚Äì Appears in an emotional flashback scene with his mom at a skatepark.

**LOCATION:** Boulder / Louisville area skatepark
**TIME:** Half-day shoot (3‚Äì5 hours)
**COMPENSATION:** Non-paid. Food, credit, and footage for reel will be provided.

**TO APPLY:**
Email **baxterdylan7@gmail.com** or call/text **(**970)406-2336 with:
‚Äì Child‚Äôs name and age
‚Äì Recent photo
‚Äì Parent/guardian contact information
‚Äì Any skateboard experience

This is a warm, character-driven scene about facing fear and finding courage.
‚Äî Dylan Lee Baxter
Writer / Director, *Under My Eyelids*

CASTING CALL for student project shooting in Leeds as part of the Northern Film School

Get in touch to star in our new film. Send us a headshot/showreel and we'll get back to you ASAP üé¨üíç

Donttellthegroomfilm@gmail.com ‚úâÔ∏èüì§

'Don't Tell the Groom' tells the story of a bride to be having second thoughts on the day of the wedding and turning to her best friend, the maid of honour, for advice. 

We're looking for 2 actresses that will display a bond of believable friendship. If you make it through auditions there'll be a round of chemistry reads to follow.

Pairs of actress friends are encouraged to email in and mention they'd like to be paired as a potential consideration for both roles. 

Looking forward to making this film. It's gonna be a good one üë∞üíí

This is an unpaid gig

Donttellthegroomfilm@gmail.com ‚úâÔ∏èüì§

'Don't Tell the Groom' tells the story of a bride to be having second thoughts on the day of the wedding and turning to her best friend, the maid of honour, for advice. 

We're looking for 2 actresses that will display a bond of believable friendship. If you make it through auditions there'll be a round of chemistry reads to follow.

Pairs of actress friends are encouraged to email in and mention they'd like to be paired as a potential consideration for both roles. 

Looking forward to making this film. It's gonna be a good one üë∞üíí

This is an unpaid gig

üé¨ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì COVENTRY UNIVERSITY FINAL YEAR FILM** üé¨

We‚Äôre currently casting for **two main characters** in our upcoming **third-year short film project**, a **horror-comedy** shooting in **Coventry** (with the possibility of additional locations ‚Äî confirmed actors will be informed in advance).

üìÖ **Filming Period:** Mid-February to March 2026
üéûÔ∏è **Length:** Approx. 15 minutes
üé≠ **Genre:** Horror Comedy

This is an **unpaid student production**, but we will **cover travel costs and catering** during filming days.

We‚Äôre looking for **dedicated and enthusiastic actors** who are passionate about working on creative projects and open to collaborating with a student film crew.

If you‚Äôre interested, please email **davist11@coventry.ac.uk** with your **headshot, showreel (if available), and a short bio**.
Once you get in touch, I‚Äôll send over **all the details about the audition process** and what to expect.

We‚Äôre aiming to **lock in our final cast by January**, so please make sure you‚Äôre available for the filming period mentioned above.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and be part of a fun and ambitious student film! üé•‚ú®

Hi there - I hope you are well and don‚Äôt mind me posting here.

We‚Äôre offering a unique theatre experience for someone who loves theatre to share the magic from a private opera box with a person from another generation ‚Äî a grandparent & grandchild, friends, or colleagues.

This filmed project, created by The Guardian and a paid partner, celebrates the joy of theatre and the connections it inspires.

**The younger participant must be 18+.**

**All participants must be based in or around London.**

If anyone you know would like to be part of this special experience, they can email stories@rosewaite.com telling us:

Their story together

Why theatre matters to them both

Please include a phone number and photos of the two of them

Shoot dates: 24 & 25 November

Paid opportunity, ¬£375 flat fee per person for both days

Please share this opportunity with family, friends and colleagues.

Thank you so much!

MY MOMMA‚ÄôS ERA: THE MUSICAL ‚Äì SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER‚ÄôS LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater ‚Äì 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It‚Äôs recommended ‚Äî not required ‚Äî for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville‚Äôs rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago ‚Äî told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago‚Äôs own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment ‚Äî it‚Äôs edutainment.

TICKETS & GROUP BENEFITS
Group rates (10+) already discounted online
Call 773-655-3575 for Senior & Youth group discounts!

Zeffy (No fees to us!):

 PayPal:

Zelle: 773-655-3575

PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS ‚Äî NOW SEEKING FINAL CREW MEMBERS

**We‚Äôre bringing a few more people aboard an already full production team for George Orwell‚Äôs *****1984*****, directed by M.A.C.**

We‚Äôre looking for:
* **Assistant Producer**
* **Social Media / Marketing** Manager
* **Sound Board Operator**
* **Lighting Board Operator**

Performances run **December 4‚Äì7, 2025** at **Three Stories Theater (937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh)**.

Our **cast and crew of over 30 artists** are already deep in rehearsals and production work, and our design team has fully built out the world of the show. We‚Äôre looking for a few final team members to join the effort and help bring this ambitious production to completion.

**ASSISTANT PRODUCER**

Supports the Executive Producer with logistics, communications, scheduling, and coordination across departments. Ideal for someone organized, proactive, and interested in hands-on producing experience in a professional theatre environment.

**SOCIAL MEDIA / MARKETING MANAGER**

Join our marketing team to help manage social channels, coordinate content posting, and support our show rollout.
We already have **two resident photographers/videographers** and a **backlog of content ready to be edited, polished, and posted**. You‚Äôll be shaping how this production is presented to the public.

SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD OPERATORS

We have professional **sound and lighting designers** who have already built out the show‚Äôs systems and cues ‚Äî we‚Äôre simply looking for **two operators** to put that design work into action during **tech week and performances**.
Experience with QLab (for Sound) or ETC lighting consoles (for Lighting) is helpful, but a good sense of focus and teamwork is most important.

**COMPENSATION TYPE:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: these are volunteer positions, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.) *

**DATES & COMMITMENTS:**
* **Rehearsals (for reference):** Sundays, 6‚Äì9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center ‚Äî 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 ‚Äì December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving)
* **Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

We‚Äôre happy to work with your schedule ‚Äî please share any known conflicts when reaching out.

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief note on your experience and interest)
* Availability during tech week and performances

If it seems like a good fit, we‚Äôll be in touch right away!

Thank you,
Marc Palombo
**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS**

MERIVENTS is Hiring!

We‚Äôre excited to assemble our Dream Team of talented professionals for iconic NYC events like SNL wrap parties, movie premieres, and sporting events.

**Building Our Dream Team**

At Amerivents, we are committed to assembling and empowering a "Dream Team" of talented individuals who bring diverse skills, shared values, and a unified purpose to every endeavor. Much like a championship sports team, we believe that our collective success is built on the strength and collaboration of our team members, each contributing their unique expertise to achieve exceptional results.

**Now Hiring FRONT OF HOUSE:**
* Catering Hospitality Staff
* Servers
* Bartenders
* Captains

**Now Hiring BACK OF HOUSE:**
* Dishwasher
* Utility
* Grill Cook
* Line Cook

**Requirements:**

2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience

You must be 18 or older

**Next Steps:**
1. Complete the interview survey here: [https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8](https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8)
2. Visit[ www.amerivents.com](http://www.amerivents.com/) and click ‚ÄúApply‚Äù (mention ‚ÄúCORE-NYC‚Äù in the referral box).

**Why Amerivents?**
* Fast-paced, exciting, and team-oriented work environment
* Flexible schedules‚Äîyou choose your availability!
* Gain unforgettable experiences in the hospitality industry
* Experience unique and inspiring event locations!

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* 2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience
* Professional, adaptable, and radiate positivity team players
* Composure under pressure and ability to adapt to dynamic environments
* Flexible and reliable team players who can seamlessly adjust to varying roles and tasks
* Ability to lift 50 lbs and stand for extended periods

**To Our Team:**
We offer the chance to pursue your passions while contributing to a company that values your unique talents and provides the support you need to excel.

We look forward to hearing from you!

**This is not an official job offer**

Angela Boehm Casting is now casting talent for a TV Pilot "The Land"! 

We are thrilled to announce a TV Pilot coming to Cleveland. We are looking for EXTRAS, TRAINED DRIVERS, STAND INS , and DOUBLES. This shoot will be split from middle of the afternoon till the middle of the night. (Times to be determined) 
This project will be taking place in the Cleveland, OH area ! 

Please read carefully below for details! 
DETAILS: 
Project: TV Pilot "The Land" Filming 
Location: Cleveland, OH area (MUST BE LOCAL) 

Shoot Date(s): November 15th, 2025 - More dates coming in the new year 
Background Rate: $120/8hr 
Trained Drivers: $120/8hr + $150 bump 
Stand In: $128/8hr Double: $136/8hr 

Link to submit: http://bit.ly/3Lki3Bb

Kind regards, Angela Boehm Casting Team 

PLEASE NOTE: This is just a submission. If you are booked, we will reach out to YOU.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì VHELMA SUE (Poster Below)**

*A 3Wize Media Short Film (12th Episode of ‚ÄúThe 13th Episode‚Äù Anthology)*

**Union Status:** SAG-AFTRA Micro-Budget Agreement
**Location:** Colorado Springs/Denver/Pueblo, CO
**Production Type:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Mystery / Supernatural Thriller
**Filming Dates:** Nov/Dec
**Compensation:** IMDB credit, meals, festival submissions, and portfolio-building opportunity
**Distribution:** This project will be submitted to multiple film festivals as part of *The 13th Episode* anthology series. 

ABOUT THE PROJECT

***VHELMA SUE*** is a short film in *The 13th Episode* Anthology Series. It follows Detective Vhelma Sue and her partner as they struggle with inner conflict while investigating a mysterious pattern of deaths linked to an unsolved childhood case. Set mostly inside a vehicle, the story unfolds through intimate dialogue, theological questions, and layered character dynamics. It connects to other award-winning films in the anthology, including *Fare Share*, *Checkmate*, and *Doc Feel Good*, forming part of a growing cinematic universe.

This is a professional but collaborative learning environment. We are open to talent at all stages of their careers, especially those looking to build IMDb credits, gain experience working under a SAG-AFTRA Micro-Budget Agreement, and collaborate with award-winning filmmakers and talent.
> 

***Note: This SAG-AFTRA Micro-Budget project cannot be used toward SAG eligibility or to gain SAG affiliation.***

SEEKING THE FOLLOWING ROLES

**(LEAD) VHELMA SUE ‚Äì Female, 30s-40s, open ethnicity**
Confident, witty, layered. Southern-born detective with a quiet past and private motivations*.**** (BONUS...not required***...***IF YOU CAN PULL OFF A SOUTHERN *****ACCENT***** AND THE LOOK IN THE POSTER!!)***

**(SUPPORTING) DETECTIVE BRYANT ‚Äì Male or Female, 30s‚Äì50s, any ethnicity**
Quick-thinking, professional. Appears in one short confirmation scene and again during an investigation. Must handle concise, convincing detective dialogue with presence.

**(SUPPORTING) DETECTIVE HERNANDEZ ‚Äì Male or Female, 30s‚Äì50s, any ethnicity**
Sharp, focused. Appears in limited screen time during an investigative sequence. Strong energy and realism preferred.

**(FEATURED) BODY OF MYA ‚Äì Female, early 20's - 30's, any ethnicity**
Portrays the body of a young woman discovered in a key scene. No lines. Must be comfortable lying still for extended takes, possibly with light FX makeup.

**(BACKGROUND EXTRAS)** ‚Äì 5 Roles Available Adults of various ages/ethnicities to appear in background scenes at police precinct, crime scene, and coffee shop. No dialogue, just naturalistic presence. Helpful for early-career actors looking to gain experience.

**SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS**

Please send the following to (or have agent send to)  **casting@3wizemedia.com** 

Headshot (professional or clear recent photo...does NOT have to be a professional photo if no H/S is available) 

Resume or reel (if available) 

City you are based in 

Role(s) you are submitting for

Availability for NOV/DEC 

Subject line: **VHELMA SUE ‚Äì [Role Name] Submission** 

NOTES This production operates under the **SAG-AFTRA Micro-Budget Agreement**. All selected talent will receive: FUN...IMDB credit On-set meals Copy of final film, festival promotion information via festival submissions, and professional experience with an award winning multi-film anthology project.

items.text:
Hey filmy friends!!!

Community is a lot like a garden. If you want a healthy, vibrant one, you gotta cultivate that shit. You gotta tend it and care for it. So, let's really dig in and build the most incredible community/garden we possibly can. 

This means ya gotta get off your tuchas and show up. Show up for events and meetings and elections and programs and festivals and screenings and all the hooooo ha. 

You want people to come see your project, ya gotta go see theirs. 
You want people to hire you, ya gotta get out and meet the people hiring. 
You want to find great people to be on your set, then ya gotta get out and meet the people you want to hire. 

Get involved!!! Sign up for shit!! Have fun!!! Make cool stuff!!! 

The next fun thing we have is this Friday. The CFVA is hosting a Halloween party. You can dress up or not, but be there! Show up. Play. Engage. Connect. It's how we will grow CO Film into something undeniable!!!! 

Come find me and say hi. I'll be busting ghosts!

Hello Everyone!

My name is Rayonna Price and I am writer/director for a short film called 'Cursed'. It is a University of Colorado Denver film.

A woman suffers through a rough day, will she get through unscathed or will someone lose their head?

Dionne and Jason have been casted for, however, we still are still looking for our Nadine and Bryce. All locations are in central Denver, and our filming dates are November 13th-16th. Transportation can be provided.

To audition and find sides follow the google link here: https://forms.gle/KJJKmE3bG3HgYHkDA

Actors will be reimbursed, please audition we would love to have you apart of production!

Thank you!

Dionne and Jason have been casted for, however, we still are still looking for our Nadine and Bryce. All locations are in central Denver, and our filming dates are November 13th-16th. Transportation can be provided.

To audition and find sides follow the google link here: https://forms.gle/KJJKmE3bG3HgYHkDA

Actors will be reimbursed, please audition we would love to have you apart of production!

Thank you!

F√ºr meinen kommenden Kurzfilm ‚ÄûZwischen Licht und Schatten‚Äú (Drehort gebe ich noch bekannt) am 10.01 und 11.01 suche ich noch engagierte Mitwirkende:

üé¨ Regie

Ich suche eine/n Regisseur:in, die/der Lust hat, gemeinsam mit mir diesen emotional intensiven Kurzfilm umzusetzen. Das Projekt ist charaktergetrieben und bewegt sich zwischen innerem Konflikt, famili√§rer Bindung und Selbstfindung.

Erfahrung ist w√ºnschenswert, aber kein Muss ‚Äî wichtiger ist Leidenschaft, Teamgeist und Gesp√ºr f√ºr authentisches Schauspiel.

üé≠ Rollen

üë©‚Äçü¶∞ Lucy (ca. 25‚Äì28 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas beste Freundin

‚Äì herzlich, empathisch, gute Zuh√∂rerin

‚Äì ruhig, aber pr√§sent, gibt Stella Halt

‚Äì Spielalter: ca. 26 Jahre

‚Äì Drehtage: [1‚Äì2]

‚Äì Keine Gage, aber Verpflegung + Material f√ºr Showreel

üë¶ Felix (Spielalter 20-22 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas j√ºngerer Bruder

‚Äì ehemals drogenabh√§ngig, heute sehr zur√ºckhaltend, manchmal verschlossen

‚Äì steht im Zwiespalt zwischen Angst und St√§rke

‚Äì hat Respekt vor Viktor (dem B√∂sewicht , drogendealer), aber kann sich im entscheidenden Moment behaupten

‚Äì Drehtage: 10.01-11.01

Kurzinhalt

Die 25-j√§hrige Stella lebt zur√ºckgezogen, misstrauisch gegen√ºber M√§nnern und misstrauisch

gegen√ºber Gef√ºhlen. Als sie im Park den sportlichen, offenen Nick kennenlernt, entsteht eine

leise N√§he ‚Äì doch Stella blockt jeden Ann√§herungsversuch ab.

W√§hrend sie langsam Vertrauen zu Nick fasst, ger√§t ihr Bruder Felix in ernste Schwierigkeiten:

Er schuldet Victor, einem gef√§hrlichen Drogendealer, 5.000 Euro. Victor bedroht Felix und sucht

schlie√ülich auch Stella auf, um an sein Geld zu kommen.

Eines Abends eskaliert die Situation. Victor lauert Stella auf ‚Äì und als Nick hinzukommt, versucht

er, sie zu sch√ºtzen. Er h√§lt ihm sein Portemonnaie mit 300 Euro hin, um Zeit zu gewinnen. Doch

Victor wird w√ºtend: ‚ÄûIch will mein Geld ‚Äì oder einer von euch stirbt!‚Äú

Nick sagt zu Stella, sie solle laufen. Zitternd flieht sie und versteckt sich hinter einem Baum.

Dann kommt es zum Kampf zwischen Nick und Victor. In einem verzweifelten Moment wird

Victor im Bauch verletzt und bricht zusammen. Als Stille einkehrt, tritt Stella hervor, ruft ‚ÄûNick!‚Äú,

l√§uft zu ihm, und beide fallen sich unter Tr√§nen in die Arme. Ein Moment zwischen Dunkelheit

und Hoffnung ‚Äì und vielleicht der Beginn einer echten Heilung.

Drehtort noch unbekannt Max im Umkreis von 200 km  von Nordhorn

üóìÔ∏è Drehzeitraum: Januar 2026

üí¨  ‚Äì gern per PN oder E-Mail an [de.pascalis1990@web.de] kontaktieren

** CASTING CALL: Are You Ready to Get **Disconnected? PAID

We‚Äôre looking for **real people** ‚Äî not actors ‚Äî to take part in a six-week challenge:
 üëâ Cut nonessential media use
 üëâ Reclaim your time
 üëâ Pursue a goal or dream you‚Äôve been putting off

This is your chance to find out what life looks like when you step away from the screen and step into your purpose.

üí≠ Maybe you‚Äôll learn a new language.
 üé∏ Write a song.
 ü™µ Build something.
 üí¨ Reconnect with someone you love.

We‚Äôll follow your journey as part of a hopeful, cinematic documentary about using technology **intentionally** ‚Äî not compulsively.

üìÖ **Filming:** 6-week period
 üìç **Location:** Anywhere in the US

‚ú® **To Apply:**
 

1Ô∏è‚É£ **Record:** Film your 3‚Äì5 minute audition video in a well-lit space, speaking clearly and authentically.

2Ô∏è‚É£ **Upload:** Upload it as a private or unlisted link (YouTube, Vimeo, or Google Drive).

3Ô∏è‚É£ **Apply:** Complete the official application form and paste your video link when prompted.

Click the link for more information and to apply:

[https://thegoodandthebeautiful.bamboohr.com/careers/100](https://thegoodandthebeautiful.bamboohr.com/careers/100)

üé¨ Short Film ‚Äú Glasses‚Äù (London)

Hi everyone,

I‚Äôm Anil an independent filmmaker currently working on a short film titled ‚ÄúGlasses‚Äù ‚Äî a heartfelt story about an encounter between two strangers.

üé• Shoot: 1‚Äì2 days in London (2nd or 3rd week of Nov 2025)

üí∞ Type: Independent short - paid, with credits, meals, and footage for reel - details will be shared and discussed once shortlisted.

Casting:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Male (25‚Äì35) ‚Äì expressive, natural, grounded.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Male (60‚Äì70) ‚Äì warm, witty, emotionally subtle.

If interested, please send a short self-tape / intro video and your availability to:

üìß angopproduction@gmail.com

I‚Äôm happy to share the script and concept note with shortlisted actors.

üé≠ TONIGHT: Queer Play Reading Club with special guest Jennifer Lunn
üìç The Railway, Clapham
üìÖ Tuesday 21 October | 7pm‚Äì11pm

Join the Queer Theatre community tonight for an evening of queer storytelling and new writing.

We‚Äôll be reading Es & Flo by Jennifer Lunn, an award-winning play about love, memory and the life two women built together behind closed doors ‚Äî coloured with memories of the Greenham Common Women‚Äôs Peace Camp, celebrating solidarity, courage and the power of chosen family. Jennifer Lunn will be joining us in person for a Q&A about her work and process.

The evening also features new writing from David Wattees, Freddie Haberfellner, and Grace Statton, giving writers and actors the chance to share work, connect and grow together in a supportive, queer-led space.

üï° Arrivals from 6:30pm (tea, coffee & snacks)
üé≠ Reading 7pm‚Äì10:30pm | Drinks & socialising after

Be part of a growing network of LGBTQIA+ artists ‚Äî join us each month as we read, create and collaborate across all Queer Theatre projects.

**Fortgeschrittene Method-Acting-Kurse **üé≠

**In Berlin & Online weltweit | Auf Deutsch & Englisch** 

Ich bin eine international arbeitende Schauspielerin, Drehbuchautorin und Schauspielcoach mit abgeschlossenem Schauspielstudium und langj√§hriger Erfahrung auf B√ºhne und vor der Kamera.

Meine Arbeit basiert auf einer fortgeschrittenen Method-Acting-Technik, entwickelt in enger Zusammenarbeit mit dem Regisseur Robert Castle (International Theatre New York) und der weltbekannten Hollywood-Coachin Susan Batson.

üé≠**Mein Ansatz**

Basierend auf der Arbeit von Stanislavski, Lee Strasberg, Stella Adler und weiterentwickelt durch Robert Castle, erm√∂gliche ich Schauspieler*innen:

items.text:
Hi 

We're looking for 11‚Äì14-year-olds across the UK to star in an Education series, My Life, My Religion. 

This exciting project, produced by CTVC will showcase the lives of young people from different faiths and worldviews. The films will be used by schools nationwide to help children learn about religion, culture and identity in a fun, friendly and inspiring way.

We want to hear from young people who are:
* ÔªøÔªøProud to share their religion or worldview (Muslim, Jewish, Buddhist, Humanist, or others).
* ÔªøÔªøConfident and curious, with lots of energy and personality.
* ÔªøÔªøSupported by a parent or guardian who is happy for them to take part.

Filming will take place in 2025/early 2026 across the UK. This is a paid opportunity, and all travel/expenses will be covered. We follow strict BBC safeguarding policies.

How to apply:

Parents/guardians should email *casting@ctvc.co.uk* with:
* ÔªøÔªøThe young person's name, age, and location
* ÔªøÔªøA short paragraph about their faith/worldview and why they'd like to take part

Please pass this opportunity on to anyone who you think will be interested in taking part. 

Best wishes,

Sam

items.text:
# (Paid) Casting for George Fox University Student Film, (Hillsboro, Oregon)

We are a group of George Fox students shooting a short film at the Airplane Home for our Location Production class, looking for a total of three non-union actors.

Project Title: Clearing The Air

Location: Airplane Home: 15270 SW Holly Hill Rd, Hillsboro, OR 97123

Safety Considerations: Dress for potential rain and cold weather. Several cats roam around the area, so be weary if you have any allergies. The actor that plays Jean will hold a non functional prop firearm.

 Shoot Dates: 10/28/2025 and 10/30/2025, 2:00PM - 9:00PM

Age Requirement: 18 and over

Pay: 50$ per day

You will receive a collection of your scenes to include in your reel.

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane‚Äôs resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could‚Äôve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a ‚ÄúKaren Carpenter‚Äù fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane‚Äôs resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could‚Äôve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a ‚ÄúKaren Carpenter‚Äù fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì Gaunt Man / Doctor (Dual Role) in Short Film *****The Damned Spot***

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s‚Äì80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional ‚Äî a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film‚Äôs psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40‚Äì85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control ‚Äî much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Send submissions to: **studio@swrco.us**
**Deadline:** **10-24-2025**

üçÇI have 5 SPOTS LEFT at my **Art of Letting Go** workshop THIS SATURDAY! This is a 3-hour acting + movement workshop that helps you release the tension you‚Äôve been carrying- in your craft, your body, and your life.

üëâYou do not need to be an artist to participate. If you‚Äôve been feeling stuck, disconnected, or just ready for a reset‚Ä¶ this is for you! It will be fun and transformative, I promise :)

items.text:
üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

Check out some of the agency sites and look at the photos, most want straightforward headshots, half body, or full shots . As already said these are too dark and they‚Äôre staged. 
A casting director is likely just to scroll past them.

Hi there - I hope you are well and don‚Äôt mind me posting here.

We‚Äôre offering a unique theatre experience for someone who loves theatre to share the magic from a private opera box with a person from another generation ‚Äî a grandparent & grandchild, friends, or colleagues.

This filmed project, created by The Guardian and a paid partner, celebrates the joy of theatre and the connections it inspires.

**The younger participant must be 18+.**

**All participants must be based in or around London.**

If anyone you know would like to be part of this special experience, they can email stories@rosewaite.com telling us:

Their story together

Why theatre matters to them both

Please include a phone number and photos of the two of them

Shoot dates: 24 & 25 November

Paid opportunity, ¬£375 flat fee per person for both days

Please share this opportunity with family, friends and colleagues.

Thank you so much!

Hello everyone,

My name is Kayuran and I‚Äôm currently working on my first short mobile horror film. The script is in progress, and I‚Äôm looking for passionate people who would like to join me on this creative journey.

I‚Äôm specifically looking for:
üé¨ A professional film editor
üé• A camera operator (based in Durban/Chatsworth area)

The goal is to work together as a team and create something special. This project isn‚Äôt about making money ‚Äî it‚Äôs about sharing stories and giving audiences an enjoyable and memorable film experience.

If you‚Äôre interested in being part of this project or know someone who might be, please feel free to reach out. Let‚Äôs build something amazing together!

From

The new Online Casting Room is here‚Äîand we‚Äôre offering something special to the first people to try it out!

The Online Casting Room simplifies and streamlines the casting process by moving it online. It‚Äôs an exclusively Canadian service that filmmakers and casting directors can use to build the cast of their dreams, and that actors can use to find their next role. Whether you‚Äôre emerging or established film talent, the Online Casting Room is here to save you time, money, and energy while extending your reach beyond your geographic location.

All you need to do to create a casting call is fill in a few quick prompts. Then, the choice to host live auditions or review self-tapes is yours. Built-in collaborative features mean your entire casting team can be involved in the process, enabling you to share notes, provide feedback, and exchange messages‚Äîall within our platform!

Our Special Offer: While right now, all access to cinewoo is free, we will be rolling out paid subscription tiers in the next future. To thank the early supporters of the Online Casting Room, we‚Äôre offering an extended 2-year free access period to our platform to everybody who posts a casting call between now and December 31, 2025 (effective when paid subscriptions are introduced). 

You have everything to gain, and nothing to lose‚Äîstep into the Online Casting Room at [www.cinewoo.com](http://www.cinewoo.com) today!

items.text:
Casting Call: The Chaos

We are seeking talented and passionate actors (18+) to join our exciting new Indie project! This is a unique opportunity to be part of a creative and collaborative production, utilizing **virtual production techniques** and **green screen technology**.

Requirements:

- Must be 18 years or older

- Comfortable performing in front of a green screen

- Enthusiastic about participating in an indie, creative-driven environment

Details:

- This is an unpaid project, but it offers a great chance to build your portfolio and gain experience in virtual production.

- Flexible scheduling for green screen scenes.

- A fantastic opportunity to work with a dedicated team on a passion project.

-IMDb Credit

If you're excited to bring unique characters to life in an innovative way, we'd love to hear from you!

To Apply:

Please submit a headshot, resume, and a brief video introduction.

They do not have to be professional!

We are looking for someone to portray these characters!

More information will be given after submission:

Chris presents himself as calm, confident, and even comforting. His tone is measured ‚Äî he doesn‚Äôt command; he invites. He speaks like a leader or preacher, someone used to controlling a room through subtle persuasion rather than force. The steady eyes, careful pouring, and soft assurances suggest someone who knows how to perform sincerity.

Underneath the calm surface, there‚Äôs a manipulative intent.

Chris Myers (African American ages 20-30)

OPEN CASTING CALL

Rose Waite Studio are looking for inter-generational pairs who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. You will get the chance to watch a live theatre show from the opera box at one of Lloyd Webber‚Äôs theatres.

You could be a grandparent and grandchild, friends or colleagues etc. who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. 

You‚Äôll need to be based in or near London. 

This is a paid opportunity. 

If you‚Äôd like to be filmed sharing your story, email stories@rosewaite.com with details of your story together and why theatre matters to you both.

Shoot dates: 24 & 25 November

Thank you!

üé∂Offering Free VIRTUAL Voice & Acting Lessons!üé∂

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a music theatre voice teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are proud to have a team of dedicated and experienced teachers who are passionate about helping students discover the joy of music. 

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, acting, violin, viola, cello, and guitar, along with 2 in person recitals each year in MI, WI, IL, and MO. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, looking to grow as a performer, or simply want to enjoy making music, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

Try a free lesson today! This is a great way to meet one of our teachers, experience a lesson, and see how music can be a fun and meaningful part of your life.

If you‚Äôd like to get started, fill out this form, and we‚Äôll match you with the teacher who‚Äôs the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

üé∂Offering Free VIRTUAL Voice & Acting Lessons!üé∂

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a music theatre voice teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are proud to have a team of dedicated and experienced teachers who are passionate about helping students discover the joy of music. 

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, acting, violin, viola, cello, and guitar, along with 2 in person recitals each year in MI, WI, IL, and MO. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you‚Äôre preparing for auditions, looking to grow as a performer, or simply want to enjoy making music, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

Try a free lesson today! This is a great way to meet one of our teachers, experience a lesson, and see how music can be a fun and meaningful part of your life.

If you‚Äôd like to get started, fill out this form, and we‚Äôll match you with the teacher who‚Äôs the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

P√• vegne af N√∏rrebro Teater leder jeg efter b√∏rn, der har lyst til at medvirke i en forestilling med pr√∏vestart i uge 45. Forestillingen har premiere d. 22. november, og spilleperioden er frem til d. 17. januar. 

Medvirken indeb√¶rer: 
* Medvirken i 1-2 scener i hver anden forestilling, s√• man ikke er p√• hver aften
* Det vil v√¶re med replikker
* Det vil v√¶re med sang. Man skal f√∏le sig komfortabel med at synge, men beh√∏ver ikke at synge rent.

Hvis det har interesse, vil jeg se frem til at h√∏re fra dig. Send mig en video med en kort pr√¶sentation samt uddrag af sang efter eget valg til [Amalieloof@gmail.com](mailto:Amalieloof@gmail.com)

K√¶re alle! Vi er et hold fra Multiplatform Storytelling and Production (MSP) i Aarhus, og skal i gang med en kort 1 dags produktion, stilet efter HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Outsider‚Äù.

üìå **Logline**

*En lille dreng er blevet brutalt myrdet, og en efterforskningsleder fors√∏ger at presse svar ud af det eneste vidne. *

Produktionen indeb√¶rer to korte scener; en forh√∏rsscene, og en scene i skoven, dagen hvor liget blev fundet. 

Til dette projekt leder vi efter f√∏lgende. K√∏n og alder er underordnet, om du er 20 eller 60, s√• send en mail:
* **Detektiven** - m√∏rk sindet noir-type, og lederen af efterforskningen. 
* **Vidnet** - forskr√¶mt hunde g√¶nger og personen der fandt liget. 

**Optagelser foreg√•r Mandag d. 27. oktober.**

üìÖTidspunktet vil v√¶re mellem 9 til 17.

üìç Alle optagelser vil foreg√• i Aarhus. 

Der vil v√¶re forsyninger og forplejning p√• set, naturligvis. 

Hvis det v√¶kker interesse for jer, s√• kontakt mig, Harald Ruby (producer) p√•:
* [MkuuAngel@gmail.com](mailto:MkuuAngel@gmail.com)
* +45 42491424

Send jeres navn, alder, vellignende billeder, samt evt. erfaring (erfaring ikke p√•kr√¶vet). 

Vi h√•ber meget I vil v√¶re med!

Harald Ruby, Anna Brahe, Anja Skov, Laurits Klinke, Valdemar Hauritz, og Victor Panduro.

CASTING CALL FOR A STUDENT SHORT-FILM!

Hi hi! My name is Megan Veto and I am a student at the Aurora Community College and will serve as the Writer/Director of this project. I am in need of actors/actresses for my Production 1 project! This will be unpaid, though I will provide anyone interested with a final version of the film. You will also be fed, so please let me know of any allergies or specific diets you may have!

Title: On the Rocks
Genre: Romantic Comedy
Logline: An angry bride walks into a bar and shakes up Ramos‚Äôs day.

SHOOTING DAYS: November 8th (10a - 6p) - 9th (1p - 7p)

LOCATION: 9075 E Lowry Blvd Denver, CO 80230

CHARACTERS:

-Ramos: The bartender. Late 20‚Äôs - early 30‚Äôs. Calm, cool, and collected. Takes care of his patrons. Wardrobe will be all black and a black button-up shirt.

-Sarah: The angry bride. Mid - late 20‚Äôs. Feisty, knows what she wants, but eventually softens under Ramos‚Äôs care. Please let me know what your dress size is so I can find a bride‚Äôs dress that fits! üòÅ

-Mike: The ex. Mid - 20‚Äôs. Flustered, desperately looking for Sarah. Cheated. Wardrobe will be black slacks and a nice white button-down shirt.

-Ruth: Sarah‚Äôs mom. 50‚Äôs. Helps Mike look for Sarah. Wardrobe will be a nice dress.

Please email me at megveto96@gmail.com with your headshot and demo reel, I will send you the script to read over.

Thank you so muc
